# Global Rules

## 1. Architecture Preference
Prefer Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) over Functional Programming (FP) for backend design.

## 2. SOLID Principles
All code must follow SOLID principles:
- Single Responsibility Principle
- Open/Closed Principle
- Liskov Substitution Principle
- Interface Segregation Principle
- Dependency Inversion Principle

## 3. Test-Driven Development (TDD)
All backend features must be developed using TDD principles.
High-level flow: tests define behavior before implementation.

## 4. Behavior-Driven Development (BDD)
All features must be defined in terms of behavior using Given / When / Then format before implementation.

## 5. No Untested Production Code
Production code must always be backed by tests before being considered complete.

## 6. Domain Isolation
Backend and frontend contexts must never be mixed unless explicitly required.